1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,521
The four dimensions are not separate personality traits.

2
00:00:03,471 --> 00:00:05,355
They form a working loop.

3
00:00:05,355 --> 00:00:07,730
Delegation chooses the right job.

4
00:00:07,730 --> 00:00:10,038
Description makes the job legible.

5
00:00:10,038 --> 00:00:12,365
Discernment evaluates the result.

6
00:00:12,365 --> 00:00:15,125
Diligence governs how the result is used.

7
00:00:15,125 --> 00:00:17,993
Each dimension creates input for the next.

8
00:00:17,993 --> 00:00:21,278
A clear delegation boundary tells you what to describe.

9
00:00:21,278 --> 00:00:25,240
A precise description creates acceptance criteria for discernment.

10
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:27,519
Discernment reveals uncertainty.

11
00:00:27,519 --> 00:00:32,451
Diligence decides whether to revise, approve, stop, or change the boundary.

12
00:00:32,451 --> 00:00:34,375
Then the loop runs again.

13
00:00:34,375 --> 00:00:38,528
If the result fails because the goal was vague, return to Delegation.

14
00:00:38,528 --> 00:00:42,240
If the AI misunderstood a constraint, improve Description.

15
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:45,451
If a claim is unsupported, strengthen Discernment.

16
00:00:45,451 --> 00:00:48,836
If the action exceeded authority, repair Diligence.

17
00:00:48,836 --> 00:00:51,932
The weakest dimension often determines the outcome.

18
00:00:51,932 --> 00:00:55,153
Excellent description cannot rescue the wrong task.

19
00:00:55,153 --> 00:00:58,750
Strong delegation cannot rescue careless evaluation.

20
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:02,432
Perfect evidence cannot justify an unauthorized action.

21
00:01:02,432 --> 00:01:04,817
Fluency requires the whole chain.

22
00:01:04,817 --> 00:01:08,317
This loop is especially useful when work is interrupted.

23
00:01:08,317 --> 00:01:14,817
Save the current goal, artifact state, unresolved question, next allowed action, and acceptance test.

24
00:01:14,817 --> 00:01:19,432
A new session can resume from evidence instead of replaying a long conversation.

25
00:01:19,432 --> 00:01:23,317
Use the loop after real tasks, not as a vague self-rating.

26
00:01:23,317 --> 00:01:30,384
Ask which decision was hardest, where rework appeared, what evidence changed your mind, and which control prevented a mistake.

27
00:01:30,384 --> 00:01:34,019
Improvement becomes visible when it changes the next workflow.

28
00:01:34,019 --> 00:01:39,355
First, treat Delegation, Description, Discernment, and Diligence as one chain.

29
00:01:39,355 --> 00:01:42,778
Second, return to the dimension that caused the failure.

30
00:01:42,778 --> 00:01:46,464
Third, preserve state and evidence so the loop can resume.
